  "instructions": [
    "1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "2. In a pan, brown the ground beef over medium-high heat until cooked, breaking it up into small pieces.",
    "3. Add the smoky chipotle peppers to the pan with the ground beef and cook for 2-3 minutes.",
    "4. Warm the tacos shells according to the package instructions.",
    "5. Assemble the tacos by spooning the beef mixture onto a shell, followed by a sprinkle of cheese and a few pickle slices.",
    "6. Drizzle lime juice over the top and sprinkle with chopped cilantro.",
    "7. Season with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "8. Serve immediately and enjoy!"
